      "scraped_at": "2026-03-13T15:35:40.695783",
      "original_context": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Touching a communal bottle of alcohol-based sanitizer will not infect you Once you've sanitized your hands, you have disinfected them from any germs that may have been on the bottle.",
      "claim_type": "fact",
      "source": "WHO",
      "source_url": "https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public/myth-busters",
      "category": "prevention",
      "scraped_at": "2026-03-13T15:35:40.695783",
      "original_context": null
    },
    {
      "text": "An alcohol-based handrub is listed as a WHO essential medicine Clean hands protect patients, health workers, other caregivers and everyone from infection.",
